• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from the cash flow statement) = -224133.22  
• Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 829755.77  

Step 2: Use the Operating Cash Flow Ratio formula:  

  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)

Step 3: Substitute the values:  

  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -224133.22 / 829755.77 ≈ -0.27

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is approximately -0.27.
